218s             This function does not have any concurrency protection, so it should
218s             generally only be called when the extraction path is a temporary
218s             directory exclusive to a single process.  This method is not
218s             automatically called; you must call it explicitly or register it as an
218s             ``atexit`` function if you wish to ensure cleanup of a temporary
218s             directory used for extractions.
